## ததஅக

[ kariñcam ]  
  
s. (க்ரௌஞ்சம்) a bird noted for its staunch love to its mate and often held and sung up by poets as a model of love which cannot brook separation  
அன்றில்  
பெ. krauñca  
1. abird celebrated by poets for its staunchattachment to its mate and held up as amodel of love which bears no separation; அன்றில். கரிஞ்சமென் றுள்ளபேர் வியூகமும் (பாரத. ஆறாம்போ. 5)